				Also I would like to add that most everyone recommends the earth elemaental, ehich I used all the way till level 8.  But then I decided to try the Water Elemental.  The little water guy is GREAT in my opinion.  The problem I had with the earth elemental is that he casts root way too often for my liking. This is great the first time to hold the mob or if the mob tries toi run, but why does he keep casting it when I would much rather that he be hitting the MOb or doing some sort of damage.  Here is where the water pet comes in, he casts an ice damage spell which, for his level is actually reasonably potent.  Yes he has less hitpoints, although from my understanding is not near as extreme as portrayed above, but he also gets hit a lot more.  The water elemental has next best hp ans gets hit a lot less.  You would think this would even them out on time they can last in a battle.  But with the water pet casting damage spells instead of ( what after the first cast i consider useless) the root spell over and over, I think he is a much better pet to use. Also it makes a large difference to equip the pet with as big a weapon as possible.  With the current version and patch he has no delay penalty so give him the best weapon possible. for example he hits for about 20 with a halberd and about 16 with a 2 handed sword. without weapons the 8th level pet only hits for about 10-12.  Hope this helps<BR>
