			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As a level 33 mage, I can say, in an outdoor zone, water is your best pet, but, fire can let you kill the blues VERY fast, and if You plan to kite, use fire, the extra damage helps.  Earth root sucks, but indoors, its your only choice unless you are grouped. In groups, always use fire. The root is enough of a taunt to keep the enemy off you while you solo indoors, but outdoors you don't need the enemy off you, you just need sow. There are uses for all the pets, and next level I get a very decent nuke... :) You people should see how much faster earth pets die compared to water. Just duel your earth and water pets. Water is the best pet, but it is the hardest to research, thats the deterent to keep it from being over used. I hope you understood that, I'm in a hurry. A good strategy is to target enemy, malise, tell pet to attack, nuke enemy, heal pet nuke enemy heal pet repeat until the thing dies. Almost always works indoors with an earth pet. Make sure you give your pet 2 swords of runes, and a burnout 2.
				</font>
